The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Tactical battle on the cards 
Kuala Lumpur, Jan. 17 (PTI): It should be a battle of tactics and nerve when defending champions Pakistan take on Australia in the final of the 13th Sultan Azlan Shah Cup hockey tournament here Sunday. Both teams have promised to play attacking hockey. Pakistan, under coach Roelant Oltmans of Holland, have adopted a style that combines the defensive formation of Europe teams while retaining the attacking flair.  Copyright 
